comment: Mozgov (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Dinwiddie (DET) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
McRae (CLE) and Tolliver (DET) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Kaun (CLE) sets the screen on Dinwiddie (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LHH and RATR show Mozgov (CLE) does not jump vertically and affects Dinwiddie's (DET) shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (DET) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with McRae (CLE) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt that is cleanly blocked by Johnson (DET).
McRae (CLE) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (DET).
Mozgov (CLE) sets the screen on Dinwiddie (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mozgov (CLE) makes incidental contact with Anthony (DET) as he attempts to defend his dunk attempt.
Mozgov (CLE) sets the screen on Tolliver (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jones (CLE) makes incidental contact with Meeks (DET) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Dinwiddie (DET) maintains a legal guarding position, and McRae (CLE) comes over his head and makes contact with his face.
Meeks (DET) splits his feet on the perimeter.
LATR shows Jones (CLE) wraps Anthony (DET), affecting his ability to roll to the basket and secure the pass.
Mozgov (CLE) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Jones (CLE) does not dislodge Meeks (DET) from his legal guarding position.
Jones (CLE) makes contact with Meeks's (DET) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Bullock (DET) makes incidental contact with Jefferson (CLE) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Jefferson (CLE) establishes a legal guarding position and is firming up as he absorbs the contact from Tolliver (DET) on the pass and crash play.
Mozgov (CLE) firms up as he sets the screen on Dinwiddie (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bullock (DET) sets the screen on Mozgov (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LHH shows that Mozgov (CLE) and Frye (CLE) make incidental contact with Dinwiddie (DET) that does not affect his RSBQ or driving shot attempt.
Frye (CLE) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (DET).
Jones (CLE) commits a take foul on Johnson (DET).
Mozgov (CLE) sets the screen on Johnson (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact. The two players make incidental contact that causes Mozgov to fall to the floor.
Johnson (DET) makes contact with McRae's (CLE) body that affects his jump shot attempt.
